				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Thinking about making a bard character<a name="64500"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 27 04 4:05 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Level 66 enchanter here that is jealous of bard abilities.  (:
<br />

<br />
I know that bards can do many things (more than any other class).  I also know that they are restricted on how many things they can do at once (up to 4 twisting songs I hear).  I know that bards make great pullers.  I know that they used to be great solo, but not sure how they are now.  I also know that I rarely see a bard lfg.  Casting Mez and other spells while running sounds awfully nice as well.  I also can imagine that twisting songs constantly is a pain.
<br />

<br />
So with that in mind, I have some questions
<br />

<br />
What is the downside to bards?  What are the limitations that you constantly run into, and wish you were as good as other classes?
<br />
Besides what I listed above, what are your upside?  Do you get invited to be the slower of groups?  Do you fulfill roles other than puller in group?
<br />
Can you effectively solo after the AE nerf?
<br />
Can you macro your twisting, or do you have to hit hotkeys for each spell each time that you twist?
<br />
Any advice for a new bard?
<br />

<br />
Thank you in advance for any advice that you can give me!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
