				<td colspan="2"><span>I find soloing gets boring MIGHTY quick, especially as a Bard.  I find soloing monotonous, a LOT of work compared to a Root&amp;Rot class, for arguably lesser gains (at least with AE Kite nerf in place).  Grouping is what being a Bard is all about.
<br />

<br />
The real beauty of the Bard is being a Jack of All Trades, the one class that can plug practically any hole.  The sheer pleasure of the variety of ways you can play your class.  The only thing really putting a dent in this ability is that we can ONLY MEM 8 (9 now) songs.  Its amazing how often I adventure in small groups and I am counted on to:
<br />
- Pull
<br />
- Slow
<br />
- Mez
<br />
- Interrupt gaters
<br />
- Haste
<br />
- Mana
<br />
- Snare
<br />
- Melee
<br />
- Debuff
<br />
- Damage Shield
<br />

<br />
I feel this is lost in large raids.  You don't really get a chance to show your wares, yet you still work just as hard usually.  I certainly am not called on to pull on raids.  Monks do that.  Twisting 3-4 songs is twisting 3-4 songs no matter which environment you are in.  The Bard is just another cog in the wheel, a cog which never seems to shine like the Clerics or Tanks or Nukers.  Undoubtedly you will be raiding with other Bards, so, you will probably be doing a couple tasks at most, since your skills really don't stack all that well.
<br />

<br />
I often play &quot;beat the Shammy&quot; on my raids.  My goal is to land my 53% slow LONG before the Shaman land theirs.  Sure, its usually on the trash mobs, but even unslowed trash mobs can quickly tear through players.
<br />

<br />
OH, and BTW, I can run super fast!!!<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
