				<td colspan="2"><span> Upside is very good, bards really are the jack of all trades class.  Seloes and fading memories are 2 of the best abilities in the game. We can avoid death better than almost any class (FD classes amy disagree with this). I went from level 38 to 52 with no deaths. We can solo at any level above about 30. I still can get decent experience chant kiting at 66, not as good as in a group but almost as good. If you have only an hour to play, you can get most of an AA just chanting with no risk. 
<br />
 Downside, other classes sometimes do not realize what a bard brings to a group. I was in a level 66-67 group in walls of slaughter the other night where the mellee toons didn't know that bard haste can get them over cap. So pickup groups at times can be hard to get. Of course we have it pretty good, since we are known as being good pullers, that alone is enough to get group invites. 
<br />
 Twisting 3-4 songs constantly even with a nostroma pad wears you down. My hand gets sore and that is a bad thing since I play guitar. You don't get much rest or get to chat when you are in a group. You really can't chat and joke around to much if your group is grinding. Of course you can always stop and chat between pulls but most people want you to bring mobs as fast as you can.
<br />
 A bid downside is that our equipment is hard to come by and as a plate class we are competing with other classes that feel that they deserve it more. In most cases, you will want to have your warrior have better gear than your bard. The upside is that we may be the least gear dependant class out there. I could chant kite solo if I had to. I have noticed that Oow seems to have some really nice droppable bard gear so far. I just traded for a ranged 1.8 percussion mod Bloodstone of the dance last night with decent all around stats. 
<br />
 So is you like to be busy when you load up EQ, a bard is definatly the class to play. But you will always be busy. I have not been in a heavy raiding guild but I hear you really only need a couple of bards on a raid. I hear bards here complaining that their role is diminished in the high end game.
<br />
 As a bard you have to be very aware of your surroundings or you can get your group killed. You said your main is an enchanter so you share some of the same responsibilities. A good bard is a great addition to a group, whereas a bad bard can cause alot of trouble. </span></td>
