				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking about making a bard character<a name="64706"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 28 04 4:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">&quot;we do have a unique ability to kill most mobs solo&quot; 
<br />

<br />
Thats a bit misleading. Any mob that doesnt summon will most likely be killed quicker by a decent ranger / shaman / Necro .. maybe even a druid.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Calinn I appreciate your viewpoint, but I apparently could have been clearer. Per your magelo and an earlier post you made,  your bard is not your main character and your bard is level 63 with 14 or so AA. Some other bards may have some experience that would add to your views. When I said that bards have a unique ability to solo many mobs, I meant it. Let me give you some examples:
<br />

<br />
1. I used to pull Glykus (a raid mob in Tactics) and kite the entire pit and all his spawned adds for loot. There are a tremendous number of casters there. Sometimes I soloed it and sometimes I duoed it with one of the top necros on my server. If you can't cast on the run, crank out mega resists and DA and fade/fd, you are not going to be able to solo this camp. I can't envision how other classes could solo this.
<br />

<br />
2. Try soloing the mephits in PON. Getting there solo is next to impossible without POV and selos. Staying there without a death pretty much requires fade. Maybe a good necro could get there and solo the camp, but I doubt it and I have never seen a necro try.
<br />

<br />
3. Unsnareable and unrootable mobs. Druids and necros and rangers usually need a mob snared or rooted. If a mob runs at SOW speed or better and it can't be snared, these classes usually won't try to solo them. Try the hobgoblins in PON for example. Some pet classes (Beastlords) solo them, but that is the only other class other than bard I have ever seen solo the hobgoblins.
<br />

<br />
4. Mez-heal. Bards can start a fight and mez the mob and heal up. This has permitted many bards to solo mobs that many other classes couldn't do.
<br />

<br />
To be sure, rangers, necros, druids, wizzies and beastlords all do more DPS than a bard as a general rule. They may be better solo classes after 65. We won't know the answer to this question for a while because it will take some time for this to shake out with new songs, spells and abilities and zones.  But from 1 to 65 if bards are not the best solo class there are few competitors. Even with the nerf to AE kites, swarm kiting up to level 65 is still some excellent experience.
<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
67 Bard, 370ish AA
<br />
